_:N44169fba56ee4cd9940b87b698dbe47b <http://schema.org/name> "Caitlin Kinsella" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
_:N44169fba56ee4cd9940b87b698dbe47b <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Caitlin Kinsella assumed the shared interim position of Government Chief People Officer for the Civil Service and Director General for <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-people-group\">the Government People Group</a> (GPG) in November 2025.</p>\n\n<p>Caitlin joined the Cabinet Office in April 2025 as Director of Employee Experience and People Performance within the GPG, where she led strategic workforce planning, oversaw initiatives to shape Civil Service culture and people insights, and led work to improve People function capability.</p>\n\n<p>Caitlin brings over 20 years of experience across government, trade union, and commercial sectors in both Australia and the UK. Prior to joining the Civil Service, she led a large-scale cultural transformation programme impacting more than 40,000 employees across 12+ countries. Notable achievements from this work include a global increase of over 24 points in employee Net Promoter Score (eNPS) and a reduction of more than 10% in the median gender pay gap.</p>\n\n<p>Outside of her professional role, Caitlin serves as a trustee for Police Now, a social enterprise dedicated to attracting exceptional and diverse individuals into neighbourhood policing.</p>\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
